            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The S&P 500 is simply a list of the 500 largest publicly traded companies in the United States, weighted by their total market value. When you 'invest in the S&P 500', you are buying a tiny piece of all 500 of those companies at once."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much money do I need to start investing in the S&P 500?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Thanks to fractional shares and zero-minimum brokerage accounts, you can start investing in the S&P 500 with as little as $1 or $5 through index funds like VOO or FXAIX."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is investing in the S&P 500 safe for beginners?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
